{"lemma":"حَلَمَة","slug":"حَلَمَة","root":"ح.ل.م","root_slug":"ح-ل-م","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ل-م","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"حَلَم","root":"حلم","pos":"N","occurrence_count":6},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":6,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":true,"sense_count":19},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8928","n8938"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D9%8E%D9%84%D9%8E%D9%85%D9%8E%D8%A9"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream (something) or about [with بِ (bi)] (something) while asleep","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to dream (something) or about [with بِ (bi)] (something) while asleep; to muse, reflect, or meditate on [with بِ (bi)]; to vision, to image","tags":["intransitive","transitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience the first seminal ejaculation; to mature physically or sexually; to attain puberty","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to experience the first seminal ejaculation; to become a legal adult or to be perceived as such","tags":["archaic","intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to mature mentally or to be perceived as such; to act or think like an adult","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to be gentle, forgiving, merciful, or lenient; to be mild-mannered","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to restrain oneself or to be restrained or checked (especially emotionally and psychologically); to forbear, to refrain, to abstain, to withhold; to be long-suffering, to be patient or enduring; to mellow","tags":["intransitive"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَمَ (ḥalama) (form I): dreaming","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a dream (something experienced during sleep); vision"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"a wish, a desire, an aspiration; a daydream (something fantasised about or desired)"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"utopia"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلَمَ (ḥalama) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"sexual maturity; puberty","examples":[{"text":"وَإِذَا بَلَغَ ٱلْأَطْفَالُ مِنْكُمُ ٱلْحُلُمَ فَلْيَسْتَأْذِنُوا كَمَا ٱسْتَأْذَنَ ٱلَّذِينَ مِنْ قَبْلِهِمْ","english":"And if the children among you reach puberty, they shall ask for permission as those who did before them."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of حَلُمَ (ḥaluma) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"mental, psychological, or comportmental maturity; prudence; rationality; discretion"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"being long-suffering, self-restraint; forbearance, longanimity","examples":[{"text":"أَنْتَ أَكْثَرُ مِنِّي حِلْمًا.","english":"You are more patient than me."},{"text":"لَا يَغُرَّنَّكَ حِلْمِي فَصَبْرِي بَدَأَ يَنْفَدُ.","english":"Let not my forbearance deceive you, for my patience is running out."}]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"tick(s), mite(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"nipple(s), teat(s)","tags":["collective"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"callous-leaved gromwell (Moltkiopsis ciliata)","tags":["collective"]}]},"etymology":{"source":"wiktextract","text":"Akin to Aramaic חֶלְמָא (ḥelmā), Classical Syriac ܚܠܡܐ (ḥelmā), Hebrew חֲלוֹם (ḥalóm), Amharic ሕልም (ḥəlm), Ugaritic 𐎈𐎍𐎎 (ḥlm). For the significations of the root in Arabic, compare م ن ي (m n y), whence أُمْنِيَة (ʔumniya, “a wish”) and مَنِيّ (maniyy, “a fluid considered conceptive; semen”)."},"ipa":["/ħulm/","/ħu.lum/"],"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8928","headword_ar":"حلّمهُ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", (S, Mgh, Msb, K,) inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHoliymN","text_ar":"تَحْلِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hil~aAmN","text_ar":"حِلَّامٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ki*~aAbN","text_ar":"كِذَّابٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"jaEalahu","text_ar":"جَعَلَهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaliymFA","text_ar":"حَلِيمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He made him to be forbearing,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clement,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.; or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he pronounced him to be so;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he called him so;"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he held,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"believed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"though, him to be so"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (S, K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he enjoined him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHilom","text_ar":"الحِلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[i. e."},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbearance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"clemency,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]: (K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he attributed to him"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlHilom","text_ar":"الحِلْم"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Mgh, Msb.)       -A2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlm","text_ar":"حلم"},{"kind":"text","text":"[so in the TA, evidently"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hl~m","text_ar":"حلّم"},{"kind":"text","text":", (see 5, its quasi-pass.,)] also signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It fattened"},{"kind":"text","text":"a lamb, or kid; said of sucking. (TA.) ―         -b2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He filled"},{"kind":"text","text":"a skin. (TA.)       -A3-  See also 1, last sentence."}],"source_refs":["S","Mgh","Msb","K"]},{"entry_id":"n8938","headword_ar":"حَلَمَةٌ","root":"Hlm","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A small tick:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a large tick;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh, Msb, K;) like"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eul~N","text_ar":"عُلٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; (S;) and said to be"},{"kind":"page_break","n":633},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"like the head"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nipple, when small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a woman's breast:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a tick in the last stage of its growth;"},{"kind":"text","text":"for at first, when small, it is called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"qamoqaAmapN","text_ar":"قَمْقَامَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HamonaAnapN","text_ar":"حَمْنَانَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quraAdN","text_ar":"قُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and then,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamapN","text_ar":"حَلَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (As, TA:) the pl., (S,) or [rather] coll. gen. n., (Mgh, Msb,) is ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamN","text_ar":"حَلَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S, Mgh, Msb.) ―         -b2-  And hence, as being likened thereto, (Mgh,) (assumed tropical:)  The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nipple, when small,"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of a woman's breast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(T, S, Mgh,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodaAnap","text_ar":"سَعْدَانَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"areola"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (T, TA;) in like manner called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"quraAdN","text_ar":"قُرَادٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (Mgh:) the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"little thing rising from the breast of a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hab~ap","text_ar":"حَبَّة"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small extuberance like a pimple"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"upon the head of the breast of a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"vuw^oluwl","text_ar":"ثُوْلُول"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"small excrescence"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in the middle of the breast of a woman:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K:) and the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"head"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"nipple"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"of each of the two breasts of a man:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb:) the two together are termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"iHalamataAn","text_ar":"ِحَلَمَتَان"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) the protuberant piece of flesh is termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamapN","text_ar":"حَلَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"as being likened in size to a large tick. (Msb.) ―         -b3-  Also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A certain worm, incident to the upper and lower skin of a sheep"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"goat,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(As, S,)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in consequence of which, when the skin is tanned, the place thereof remains thin:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a certain worm, incident to skin, which it eats, so that, when the skin is tanned, the place of the eating rends:"},{"kind":"text","text":"pl. [or rather coll. gen. n.] ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HalamN","text_ar":"حَلَمٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (K.)       -A2-  And"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A species of plant;"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K;) accord. to As,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"also called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"yanamapN","text_ar":"يَنَمَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":": (S:) As is also related to have said that it is"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plant of the kind termed"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Eu$ob","text_ar":"عُشْب"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a dusty hue, a rough feel, and a red flower:"},{"kind":"text","text":"another says that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it grows in Nejd, in the sands, has a blossom, and roughish leaves, and thorns resembling the nails of a man;"},{"kind":"text","text":"and that"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the camels suffer adhesion of the spleen to the side, and their young are cast,"},{"kind":"text","text":"[for"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"wtzl","text_ar":"وتزل"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AxyAkhA","text_ar":"اخياكها"},{"kind":"text","text":"(an evident mistranscription in the TA), I read"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"watzil~u A^aHobaAluhA","text_ar":"وَتزِلُّ اَحْبَالُها"},{"kind":"text","text":",]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"when they depasture it from the dry branches:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to AHn, it is ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"less than a cubit"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in height"},{"kind":"text","text":"],"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"having a thick,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rough, leaf, and branches, and a flower like that of the anemone, except that it is larger, and thicker,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"rougher:"},{"kind":"text","text":"accord. to the K, it signifies also the"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"tree"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"plant"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"called"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"saEodaAn","text_ar":"سَعْدَان"},{"kind":"text","text":"; which is one of the most excellent kinds of pasture: but Az says, it has nothing in common with the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"sEdAn","text_ar":"سعدان"},{"kind":"text","text":", which is a herb having round [heads of] prickles; whereas the"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Hlmp","text_ar":"حلمة"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"has no prickles, but is a well-known kind of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"janobap","text_ar":"جَنْبَة"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and I have seen it: (TA:) [Dmr, accord. to Golius, describes it as “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a herb less than the arnoglossa"},{"kind":"text","text":"” (or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"arnoglossum"},{"kind":"text","text":"), “"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"whitening in the leaves, and downy."},{"kind":"text","text":"”]"}],"source_refs":["K","Msb","As","TA","S","Mgh","T"]}]}}